## Common Rules Summary

### Coding Style (`.bbg/harness/rules/common/coding-style.md`)
- Small, focused functions (<50 lines)
- Descriptive naming conventions
- Consistent formatting and indentation
- Meaningful comments for complex logic

### Git Workflow (`.bbg/harness/rules/common/git-workflow.md`)
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- Branch naming: `feature/`, `fix/`, `refactor/`, `docs/`
- PR workflow: analyze changes, draft summary, include test plan

### Testing (`.bbg/harness/rules/common/testing.md`)
- Write tests before implementation (TDD)
- Coverage target: 80%+
- Unit tests for business logic, integration tests for workflows

### Security (`.bbg/harness/rules/common/security.md`)
- No hardcoded secrets
- Validate all user inputs
- Sanitize file paths
- Parameterized database queries
- No sensitive data in error messages

### Performance (`.bbg/harness/rules/common/performance.md`)
- Lazy-load heavy dependencies
- Async/await for I/O operations
- Avoid blocking the event loop

